                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">Editorial Note</hi>
                </head>
                <p>No official record of the substance of the discussion at this meeting has been
                    found. The information set forth above is derived from the President’s
                    appointment calendar (Roosevelt Papers) and from Alanbrooke, p. 331. Alanbrooke
                    indicates that the sending of American reinforcements to the Middle East came
                    under discussion. For Marshall’s memorandum to Roosevelt on the subject of
                    American forces in the Middle East, which was sent to the President on June 23,
                    see <hi rend="italic">post</hi>, <ref target="#pg_476">p. 476</ref>.</p>
            </div>
        </body>
